aters that give and sustain all life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aIndians of North AmericaxSocial life and customs. 0aTraditional ecological knowledge. 7aNATURE / General.2bisacsh  aecology, indigenous peoples studies, lineage, ecological connections, society, social issues, spirituality, responsibility, conservation, traditions, culture, new systems, human behavior, essays, interviews, poetry, poems, linda hogan, wendell berry, winona laduke, vandana shiva, robin kimmerer, wes jackson, descendants, relationships, healing, ancestors, indians of north america, traditional knowledge, customs.1 aAbeyta, Aaron A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBayens, Leah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBray, Kaylena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalvert, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColeman, Taiyon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCummings, Katherine Kassouf, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDean Moore, Kathleen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForbes, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGibney, Shannon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuttierez, Oscar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHausdoerffer, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHausdoerffer, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHecht, Brooke Parry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHecht, Brooke Parry, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHerron, Elizabeth Carothers, econtribut